just_use helpers.go

# label: CANONICAL
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Cross-cutting view helpers: PageHeader / PageFooter / PageSubtitle /
RequireAuth / UserLink. Every hand-written view and every generated view
(via crudgen-emitted code) calls through here, so layout and auth are
consistent.

lastAuthUserID is a module-level var set by RequireAuth and read by
PageHeader so the nav bar can render "logged in as X" without each handler
re-authenticating. Side-effect-y but scoped to one request's goroutine by
design (single DB connection → request serialization).

Not a page; stays hand-written.
